class SensorSystem {
    public int temperature = 0;
    public boolean alarm = false;

    public void increaseTemp(int increment) {
        temperature += increment;
        if (temperature > 100) {
            alarm = true;
        }
    }

    public void resetAlarm() {
        if (temperature <= 100) {
            alarm = false;
        }
    }

    public void emergencyShutdown() {
        temperature = 0;
        alarm = false;
    }
}",

If we observe that the alarm is true, can we conclude that the temperature was definitively higher than 100 before any potential resetAlarm call?
